title: Only friends (Prologue/7)  [Peter Parker x Reader]
body:
Summary: Peter Parker was many things, but Y/N didn’t expected him to be the love of her life (fluff, little angst)

Words: 270 +/- (it’s a prologue, be kind, pls)

Warnings: Flash isn’t a pain in the ass; Peter isn’t so shy 

*Part 1* *Part 2* *Part 3* *Part 4* *Part 5* *Part 6* 

Peter Parker was a hero.

I remember the first time he saved me; I was just a little girl with crooked legs and ponytail when I met him.

It was a rather comical situation, we might say.

The thing was, we were in first grade, and I was extremely in need to pee. It was the second day of school and the teacher had left the room for a few minutes to get some handouts for the students who had missed the day before. Since Flash was the oldest in the class, he would be responsible for keeping an eye on the students in those short minutes that the teacher would be absent, and she had told him not to let anyone leave. So I just peed myself; and that’s where my despair began.

When the pee began to dribble from the chair to the floor, afraid that someone would see it and I would become a joke, I took a face wash that was part of the students’ personal items and started trying to wipe the pee. Realizing my despair, the boy stared at me and approached, asking if I had any problems. But as soon as he smelled the urine, he frowned and said, “I’ll help you, I have extra pants in my backpack. Come with me.” And he took my small hand as he dragged me into the bathroom. As my tears came down, he tried to make sure that peeing in the pants is the most normal thing of the world.

That was the first time Peter saved me, and also, when I met my best friend.

Taglist: @tokoyamisstuff ​ aaaaand that’s it

A/N: I don’t really have anything to say, just hope you liked it. Oh, I’ll be posting a chapter of this every saturday, stay tuned

send me an ask or message if you want to be on my taglist and which one you want (Bucky, Peter, Avengers, all of them…)
